Category:Spanish-language albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Mark Taylor]]\n", "text_old": "{{other uses of}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Sex and Love\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Enrique Iglesias]]\n| cover      = Sex and Love.png\n| border     = yes\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{start date|df=yes|2014|03|14}}\n| recorded   = 2012\u201314\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{flatlist|\n* [[Latin pop]]<ref>[http://www.popmatters.com/review/180038-enrique-iglesias-sex-and-love/ Enrique Iglesias: SEX AND LOVE &#124; PopMatters] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140320125740/http://www.popmatters.com/review/180038-enrique-iglesias-sex-and-love/ |date=20 March 2014 }}</ref>\n* [[electropop]]\n* [[dance-pop]]<ref>[http://www.newsday.com/entertainment/music/enrique-iglesias-sex-and-love-review-slick-spanglish-dance-pop-1.7394863 Enrique Iglesias' 'Sex and Love' review: Slick, Spanglish dance pop - Newsday] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140420050457/http://www.newsday.com/entertainment/music/enrique-iglesias-sex-and-love-review-slick-spanglish-dance-pop-1.7394863 |date=20 April 2014 }}</ref>\n}}\n| length     = {{duration|m=38|s=06}}\n| language   = {{flatlist|\n* English\n* Spanish\n* Portuguese\n}}\n| label      = [[Republic Records|Republic]]\n| producer   = {{flatlist|\n* [[The Cataracs]]\n* Mark Taylor\n* Carlos Paucar\n* [[DJ Frank E]]\n* Descemer Bueno\n* [[RedOne]]\n* [[Marty James]]\n* [[Rome Ramirez|Rome]]\n* Metrophonic\n* [[Romeo Santos]]\n* [[soFLY & Nius]]\n* [[Alex P]]\n}}\n| prev_title = [[Euphoria (Enrique Iglesias album)|Euphoria]]\n| prev_year  = 2010\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Sex and Love\n | type        = Studio\n | single1     = [[Finally Found You]]\n | single1date = 17 September 2012\n | single2     = [[Turn the Night Up]]\n | single2date = 15 July 2013\n | single3     = [[Loco (Enrique Iglesias song)|Loco]]\n | single3date = 26 August 2013\n | single4     = [[Heart Attack (Enrique Iglesias song)|Heart Attack]]\n | single4date = 16 September 2013\n | single5     = [[El Perdedor (Enrique Iglesias song)|El Perdedor]]\n | single5date = 28 October 2013\n | single6     = [[I'm a Freak]]\n | single6date = 13 January 2014\n | single7     = [[Bailando (Enrique Iglesias song)|Bailando]]\n | single7date = 3 February 2014\n | single8     = [[Noche y De D\u00eda]]\n | single8date = 5 January 2015\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Sex and Love''''' is the tenth [[studio album]] recorded by Spanish recording artist [[Enrique Iglesias]]. It was released on 14 March 2014 by [[Republic Records]]. The album's three Spanish singles: \"[[Loco (Enrique Iglesias song)|Loco]]\", \"[[El Perdedor (Enrique Iglesias song)|El Perdedor]]\" and \"[[Bailando (Enrique Iglesias song)|Bailando]]\" reached No. 1 on the ''Billboard'' [[Hot Latin Songs]] chart. The album features guest vocals from [[Jennifer Lopez]], [[Kylie Minogue]], [[Descemer Bueno]], [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]], [[Flo Rida]], Anthony Touma, [[Romeo Santos]], [[Mickael Carreira]], [[Marco Antonio Sol\u00eds]], [[Yandel]], [[Gente de Zona]], [[Luan Santana]], [[India Mart\u00ednez]] and [[Sean Paul]]. ''Sex and Love'' won the [[Lo Nuestro Award for Pop Album of the Year]].\n\n==Background==\nIn an interview Enrique explained the reason behind titling his new album as ''Sex and Love''. He said: \"It's one of the first things I thought about when I listened to the whole body of work. I think it's something we can all relate to no matter what religion no matter what personality, no matter what colour we can all relate to it.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv3.ie/entertainment_article.php?locID=1.803.810&article=126162 |title=Enrique Iglesias thinks legs are sexy - TV3 Xpos\u00e9 Entertainment |publisher=Tv3.ie |date=12 February 2014 |accessdate=11 April 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\nSpeaking about his album Enrique described his album as fun and obviously sexual, while some of it is more introspective and nostalgic. He then went on to say: \"The words go together, but they can be separate and inspire different feelings and thoughts. It's all-encompassing. When you turn on the radio, what are the themes that everybody relates to? We all relate to sex and love. That's why when you hear music&nbsp;\u2013 90% of the time&nbsp;\u2013 it derives from those two feelings.\"{{citation needed|date=August 2015}}\n\n==Release and promotion==\nThis album became available for pre-order on 15 February 2014 through [[Topspin Media]]. Two versions of the album (the standard containing 11 tracks and the deluxe with 5 bonus tracks) are available, both physically and digitally.<ref name=\"Pre-order\">{{cite web | url=http://labs.topspin.net/artists/enriqueiglesias/sexandlove/ | title=Enrique Iglesias Sex & Love | publisher=Topspin Media | date=15 February 2014 | accessdate=15 February 2014| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140225034517/http://labs.topspin.net/artists/enriqueiglesias/sexandlove/ | archivedate=25 February 2014 }}</ref><ref name=\"Pre-order%2520Announcenent%2520on%2520Facebook%2520\">{{cite web | url=https://www.facebook.com/Enrique/photos/a.128331853123.105821.19061333123/10152035990743124/?type=1&stream_ref=10 | title=#SEXANDLOVE album pre-order is live | publisher=Facebook | work=Enrique Iglesias | date=15 February 2014 | accessdate=15 February 2014}}</ref> A special deluxe edition for [[Target Corporation|Target]] and [[Walmart]] is also available, which contains two bonus tracks. The album became available for pre-order via iTunes in the United States, Canada and Mexico on 4 March 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/sex-and-love/id829282622 |title=iTunes - Music - SEX AND LOVE by Enrique Iglesias |publisher=Itunes.apple.com |date=18 March 2014 |accessdate=11 April 2014}}</ref> The pre-order was available for rest of the world on 5 March 2014. A 30-second sample was released on iTunes for each track.\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Critical reception===\n{{Album ratings\n| MC        = 54/100<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/sex-and-love/enrique-iglesias|title=Reviews for Sex and love by Enrique Iglesias}}</ref>\n| rev1      = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"AMG\">{{cite web |first=Stephen Thomas |last=Erlewine |title=Review: ''Sex And Love'' |url={{AllMusic|class=album|id=mw0002619796|pure_url=yes}} |publisher=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=17 March 2014}}</ref>\n| rev2      = [[ArtistDirect]]\n| rev2Score = {{rating|5|5}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Review: ''Sex And Love, A Masterpiece by Enrique'' |url=http://www.artistdirect.com/entertainment-news/article/enrique-iglesias-sex-and-love-album-review-5-out-of-5-stars/10916832|publisher=[[Artistdirect]] |accessdate=24 March 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140325102808/http://www.artistdirect.com/entertainment-news/article/enrique-iglesias-sex-and-love-album-review-5-out-of-5-stars/10916832|archivedate=25 March 2014}}</ref>\n|rev3       = ''[[The Boston Globe]]''\n|rev3score  = (favorable)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/music/2014/03/17/album-review-enrique-iglesias-sex-and-love/NKqRBcgcxjTdSn7m6tKWXO/story.html|title=Enrique Iglesias, \"Sex And Love\"|publisher=Boston Globe|accessdate=18 March 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140320142820/http://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/music/2014/03/17/album-review-enrique-iglesias-sex-and-love/NKqRBcgcxjTdSn7m6tKWXO/story.html|archivedate=20 March 2014}}</ref>\n| rev4      = [[Speakeasy Mag|Culture Fix]]\n| rev4Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"culturefix\">{{cite web |title=Review: ''Sex And Love'' |url=http://www.culturefix.co.uk/2014/03/album-review-enrique-iglesias-sex-love.html|publisher=Culture Fix|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140325203944/http://www.culturefix.co.uk/2014/03/album-review-enrique-iglesias-sex-love.html|archivedate=25 March 2014}}</ref>\n| rev5      = ''[[Daily Star (United Kingdom)|Daily Star]]''\n| rev5Score = {{rating|3|5}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Review: ''Sex And Love'' |url=http://www.dailystar.co.uk/showbiz/playlist/369841/Leading-by-Example-This-week-s-big-single-and-album-releases|publisher=[[Daily Star (United Kingdom)|Daily Star]] |accessdate=17 March 2014}}</ref>\n| rev6      = [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]\n| rev6Score = {{rating|3|5}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Review: ''Sex And Love'' |url=http://www.idolator.com/7510262/enrique-iglesias-sex-love-album-review|publisher=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |accessdate=18 March 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140318153440/http://www.idolator.com/7510262/enrique-iglesias-sex-love-album-review|archivedate=18 March 2014}}</ref>\n| rev7      = ''[[Jake Hamilton|Jake's Take]]''\n| rev7Score = (B)<ref>{{cite web |title=Enrique's Sex And Love (2014)|url=http://jakes-take.com/2014/03/new-music-releases-week-of-march-17-2014|accessdate=17 March 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140318232045/http://jakes-take.com/2014/03/new-music-releases-week-of-march-17-2014/|archivedate=18 March 2014}}</ref>\n| rev8      = ''[[Newsday]]''\n| rev8Score = (B)<ref name=\"EW\">{{cite web |title=Sex And Love (2014) - Enrique Iglesias |url=http://www.newsday.com/entertainment/music/enrique-iglesias-sex-and-love-review-slick-spanglish-dance-pop-1.7394863|accessdate=17 March 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140420050457/http://www.newsday.com/entertainment/music/enrique-iglesias-sex-and-love-review-slick-spanglish-dance-pop-1.7394863|archivedate=20 April 2014}}</ref>\n| rev9      = ''[[PopMatters]]''\n| rev9Score = {{rating|2.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web|last1=Faulkner|first1=Brent|title=Enrique Iglesias: SEX AND LOVE|url=http://www.popmatters.com/review/180038-enrique-iglesias-sex-and-love/|website=PopMatters|accessdate=10 June 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n\nThe ''[[Daily Star (United Kingdom)|Daily Star]]'' gave the album 3 out of 5 stars stating that \"Iglesias has turned all sleazy Robin Thicke slurring: 'I've been spending all my money on these pretty girls and alcohol, but honey, they got nothing on you' over the funky 'Let Me Be Your Lover'.\" However they praised \"Loco\", stating that it will have fans \"getting their Latin freak on\". ''AllMusic'' also gave the album 3/5, stating \"Iglesias walks the line between the dancefloor jams of 2007's ''Insomniac'' and the romantic flavor of 2010's ''Euphoria''.\" They chose \"Bailando\", \"El Perdedor\", \"Let Me Be Your Lover\" and \"Loco\" as the best songs from the album.<ref>{{cite web|author=Thom Jurek |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/sex-and-love-mw0002619796 |title=Sex and Love - Enrique Iglesias &#124; Songs, Reviews, Credits, Awards |publisher=AllMusic |date=18 March 2014 |accessdate=11 April 2014}}</ref> ''[[Newsday]]'' gave the album a \"B\" grade and described the album as \"slick, state-of-the-art Spanglish dance pop\". ''Idolator'' gave the album 3/5 stars and called the album ''[[Euphoria (Enrique Iglesias album)|Euphoria]]''{{'}}s \"older cousin\". They stated that the album isn't his greatest but there's enough decent material to remind you of what Enrique is capable of at full flight. They named \"You & I\" and \"Bailando\" as the best singles from the album.<ref name=\"EW\"/>\n\nJake Hamilton of ''Jake's Take'' gave the album a \"B\" grade stating that he went overboard on the Spanish tracks. He also praised Iglesias work in co-writing every song on the album. [[The Boston Globe]] gave a favorable review stating that Enrique \"remains a heartthrob for a reason.\" They also said that \"You and I\" is \"filled with romantic yearning,\" while his duet with Kylie Minogue, \"Beautiful,\" \"manages to be corny yet endearing.\" They concluded that \"It\u2019s the heat not the beat that brings out the best in Iglesias.\" [[Artistdirect]] gave a positive review and gave the album 5/5 stars stating that the new album is Enrique's biggest and boldest masterpiece yet. They described the song \"Noche Y Dia\" as one of the most powerful and potent Latin anthems ever.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.culturefix.co.uk/2014/03/album-review-enrique-iglesias-sex-love.html |title=Album Review: Enrique Iglesias - Sex + Love |publisher=Culture Fix |date= |accessdate=11 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140325203944/http://www.culturefix.co.uk/2014/03/album-review-enrique-iglesias-sex-love.html|archivedate=25 March 2014}}</ref> ''Culture Fix'' took note of the album's range of styles stating \"The club-friendly tracks are slickly produced and filled with a high-octane energy, the ballads are complete with a raw charisma and emotion, and the mid-tempo tracks hark back to some of the singer's best work,\" scoring the album 4/5.<ref name=\"culturefix\"/>\n\n===Commercial performance===\n''Sex and Love'' debuted at No. 8 on US ''Billboard'' 200, selling 24,000 copies in its first week. It is Iglesias's third ''Billboard'' top 10 album after ''[[Euphoria (Enrique Iglesias album)|Euphoria]]'' (No. 10) and ''[[Escape (Enrique Iglesias album)|Escape]]'' (No. 2).<ref>{{cite news|first=Keith|last=Caulfield|title='Frozen' Earns Its Biggest Sales Week Yet, Tops Billboard 200 a Seventh Time|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6006529/frozen-earns-its-biggest-sales-week-yet-tops-billboard-200-a-seventh-time|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|date=March 26, 2014|accessdate=March 26, 2014}}</ref> The album also entered the top 10 of the [[Canadian Albums Chart]]. It peaked at No. 1 on the [[Billboard Top Latin Albums|Top Latin Albums]] and [[Latin Pop Albums]] charts simultaneously. It peaked at No. 11 on the [[UK Albums Chart]], selling an approximate of 7,500 copies in first week. It also peaked at No. 6 on the [[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|Spanish Albums Chart]]. The album received a gold certification within the second week of its release in Mexico. ''Sex and Love'' was certified double platinum by the [[RIAA]] in the Latin field for shipping over 120,000 copies; furthermore has sold 174,000 copies since its release in March in United States.<ref name=ussales>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/6436399/nielsen-music-soundscan-2014-taylor-swift-republic-records-streaming?page=0%2C3|title=Music in 2014: Taylor Takes the Year, Republic Records on Top, Streaming to the Rescue|last=Christman|first=Ed|work=Billboard |publisher=Prometheus Global Media |date= 9 January 2015 |accessdate=10 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Singles==\n* \"[[Finally Found You]]\" was released as a single on 17 September 2012. The track features vocals from rapper [[Sammy Adams]]. Commercially, the song managed to reach the top twenty in [[Canada]] and the top forty in [[Australia]], [[Spain]] and [[United States]], also topping the [[Hot Dance Club Songs]] chart. However, this song was only included on the international deluxe edition of ''Sex and Love''. \n* \"[[Turn the Night Up]]\" was released as the second single from the album and the song debuted at number 30 on the [[Pop Songs]] chart and at number 6 on [[Dance/Electronic Digital Songs]], while also debuting at number 62 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|Hot 100]]. \n* \"[[Loco (Enrique Iglesias song)|Loco]]\" was released as the third single from the album and features guest vocals from Bachata singer [[Romeo Santos]]. The single reached No. 1 in Spain, Mexico and the Dominican Republic. Moreover, it also became Iglesias' 23rd No. 1 single on the Hot Latin Tracks chart and 18th No. 1 single on the Latin Pop Airplay chart. It was also ranked at No. 9 on the ''Billboard'' Year-End Hot Latin Songs chart for 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin-notas/5748225/enrique-iglesias-widens-lead-for-most-no-1s-on-latin-songs |title=Enrique Iglesias Widens Lead for Most No. 1s on Hot Latin Songs Chart |publisher=Billboard |date= |accessdate=11 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131013004946/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin-notas/5748225/enrique-iglesias-widens-lead-for-most-no-1s-on-latin-songs|archivedate=13 October 2013}}</ref>\n* \"[[Heart Attack (Enrique Iglesias song)|Heart Attack]]\" was released as the fourth single from the album. It was released exclusively in North America. It peaked at No. 88 on US ''Billboard'' Hot 100 and No. 83 on Canadian Hot 100. It also reached No. 26 on US Mainstream Top 40, making it Iglesias' 16th entry on that chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/301773/Enrique+Iglesias/chart?f=381 |title=Enrique Iglesias - Chart history |publisher=Billboard |date= |accessdate=11 April 2014}}</ref> \n* \"[[El Perdedor (Enrique Iglesias song)|El Perdedor]]\" was released as the fifth single from the album. It features guest vocals from [[Marco Antonio Solis]]. It serves as the opening theme of Mexican telenovela ''[[Lo Que La Vida Me Rob\u00f3]]'' (2013-2014). This is the fifth time that Enrique's song is chosen as an opening theme of a telenovela after \"Cosas del Amor\", \"Nunca Te Olvidar\u00e9\", \"Cuando Me Enamoro\", \"Marisol\" (Por Amarte) and \"El Pa\u00eds de las Mujeres\" (Ruleta Rusa). It became Iglesias' 24th No. 1 single on the Hot Latin Songs chart and 19th No. 1 single on the Latin Pop Airplay chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin-notas/5892790/enrique-iglesias-scores-24th-no-1-sex-love-album-art |title=Enrique Iglesias Scores 24th No. 1, Reveals Album Title 'Sex+Love' |publisher=Billboard |date= |accessdate=11 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140408213249/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin-notas/5892790/enrique-iglesias-scores-24th-no-1-sex-love-album-art|archivedate=8 April 2014}}</ref> \n* \"[[I'm a Freak]]\" was released as the sixth single from the album and the first one to be released worldwide. The song features Cuban-American rapper [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]]. The song became a commercial success in Europe peaking within the top ten in the United Kingdom, Spain, Ireland, Finland and Serbia. It peaked at No. 45 in Australia and No. 52 in Canada. It also peaked at No. 38 on US Mainstream Top 40 chart, making it Iglesias' 17th entry on that chart.\n* \"[[Bailando (Enrique Iglesias song)|Bailando]]\" was the seventh single to be released from the album.<ref name=chileoro>{{cite web|url=http://www.carolina.cl/musica/2014/04/enrique-iglesias-presenta-su-nuevo-single-bailando/|title=Enrique Iglesias presenta su nuevo single \"Bailando\"|publisher=Carolina 99.3|language=Spanish|accessdate=8 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140408225031/http://www.carolina.cl/musica/2014/04/enrique-iglesias-presenta-su-nuevo-single-bailando/|archivedate=8 April 2014}}</ref> It became Iglesias' 25th No. 1 single on the Hot Latin Songs chart and 20th No. 1 single on the Latin Pop Airplay chart. It holds the number 38 spot on the [[Billboard Year-End Hot 100 singles of 2014]] chart. The Spanish version of the song acts as the opening theme of telenovela Reina de Corazones.\n* \"[[Noche y De D\u00eda]]\" was released as an eighth and final single on 1 April 2015 and was certified platinum in Spain and gold in Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/cl/album/Noche-y-dia-feat.-yandel-juan/id979220399?%7c=en|title=iTunes - M\u00fasica - Noche y de D\u00eda (feat. Yandel & Juan Magan) - Single de Enrique Iglesias|work=iTunes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.de/gp/product/B00V7BFI9Y?ie=UTF8&at=&force-full-site=1&ref_=aw_bottom_links|title=Noche Y De Dia [feat. Juan Magan]|work=amazon.de}}</ref> It will be officially sent to radio stations in Italy on 3 July 2015.<ref>http://www.radioairplay.fm/radio-date/ENRIQUE-IGLESIAS--Noche-Y-De-Dia-(feat.-Yandel-&-JUan-Magan)-133637-03-07-2015</ref>\n* \"[[Beautiful (Enrique Iglesias and Kylie Minogue song)|Beautiful]]\", featuring [[Kylie Minogue]], was released as the first promotional single on 14 March 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/beautiful-feat.-kylie-minogue/id839853131|title=iTunes - Music - Beautiful (feat. Kylie Minogue) - Single by Enrique Iglesias|work=iTunes}}</ref> \n*\"There Goes My Baby\" was released as the second promotional single only in the UK in May 2014.\n*\"Let Me Be Your Lover\", featuring Anthony Touma instead of Pitbull, was released as third promotional single in France on 22 September 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/fr/album/let-me-be-your-lover-feat./id929243070|title=iTunes - Musique - Let Me Be Your Lover (feat. Anthony Touma) [French Remix] - Single par Enrique Iglesias|work=iTunes}}</ref>\n\n===Other songs===\n\"[[I Like How It Feels]]\" was released as a digital download in Australia and some European countries on 23 September 2011. The song was released as a [[Music download|digital download]] in the United States on 4 October 2011. The song originally intended to be the lead single from a reissue of Iglesias' album ''[[Euphoria (Enrique Iglesias album)|Euphoria]]'', however, the release was cancelled after poor chart performance from the song. The song was later included on the international deluxe edition of ''Sex and Love''.\n\n==Tour==\n{{Main|Sex and Love Tour}}\nIglesias started a promo tour on 14 February 2014, which took place in San Juan, Puerto Rico.{{cn|date=March 2020}} The next day he performed at a sold-out concert at the [[Madison Square Garden]] in New York.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music-arts/enrique-iglesias-set-heat-msg-valentine-weekend-concert-article-1.1612084 |title=Enrique Iglesias set to heat up Madison Square Garden with Valentine\u2019s weekend concert |publisher=NY Daily News |date=12 February 2014 |accessdate=11 April 2014}}</ref> He is set to perform in Dia Anahuac, Mexico on 27 February 2014.<ref>{{cite web|author=Added by Enrique Iglesias View Events |url=http://www.enriqueiglesias.com/events/mexico-dia-anahuac |title=Mexico - D\u00eda Anahuac - Enrique Iglesias - Official Website |publisher=Enrique Iglesias |date= |accessdate=11 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302155331/http://www.enriqueiglesias.com/events/mexico-dia-anahuac|archivedate=2 March 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe tour will officially kick-off from Santiago, [[Chile]], where Iglesias will perform on 20 May 2014.<ref>{{cite web|author=Added by Zach from EI Team View Events |url=http://www.enriqueiglesias.com/events/santiago-chile |title=5/20 - Santiago, Chile - SEX AND LOVE TOUR - Enrique Iglesias - Official Website |publisher=Enrique Iglesias |date= |accessdate=11 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407072517/http://www.enriqueiglesias.com/events/santiago-chile|archivedate=7 April 2014}}</ref> Two days later on 22 May 2014 he performed  at [[Luna Park, Buenos Aires|Luna Park]] in Buenos Aires, Argentina.<ref>{{cite web|author=Added by Enrique Iglesias View Events |url=http://www.enriqueiglesias.com/events/5-22-buenos-aires-argentina-sex-and-love-tour |title=5/22 - Buenos Aires, Argentina - SEX AND LOVE TOUR - Enrique Iglesias - Official Website |publisher=Enrique Iglesias |date=2 April 2014 |accessdate=11 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407073220/http://www.enriqueiglesias.com/events/5-22-buenos-aires-argentina-sex-and-love-tour |archivedate=7 April 2014 }}</ref> A second leg of the tour will visit North America in Fall 2014, and will be co-headlined by [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]]. This is the second time that the two Latino stars have toured together with [[Euphoria Tour (Enrique Iglesias)|Euphoria Tour]] being their first.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://top40.about.com/b/2014/03/18/pitbull-and-enrique-iglesias-announce-fall-2014-concert-tour.htm |title=Pitbull and Enrique Iglesias Announce Fall 2014 Concert Tour |publisher=Top40.about.com |date=18 March 2014 |accessdate=11 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407065154/http://top40.about.com/b/2014/03/18/pitbull-and-enrique-iglesias-announce-fall-2014-concert-tour.htm |archivedate=7 April 2014 }}</ref>\nElsewhere he is performing in Mexico on 29 May 2014, 30 May 2014 and on 1 June 2014. [[Demi Lovato]] will be the opening act for few of the dates in the United Kingdom and Europe.<ref>{{cite web|author=Added by Enrique Iglesias View Events |url=http://www.enriqueiglesias.com/events/5-29-mexico-city-sex-and-love-tour |title=5/29 - Mexico City, Mexico - SEX AND LOVE TOUR - Enrique Iglesias - Official Website |publisher=Enrique Iglesias |date= |accessdate=11 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407075150/http://www.enriqueiglesias.com/events/5-29-mexico-city-sex-and-love-tour|archivedate=7 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Added by Enrique Iglesias View Events |url=http://www.enriqueiglesias.com/events/5-30-mexico-city-mexico-sex-and-love-tour |title=5/30 - Mexico City, MEXICO - SEX AND LOVE TOUR - Enrique Iglesias - Official Website |publisher=Enrique Iglesias |date= |accessdate=11 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407075012/http://www.enriqueiglesias.com/events/5-30-mexico-city-mexico-sex-and-love-tour|archivedate=7 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Added by Enrique Iglesias View Events |url=http://www.enriqueiglesias.com/events/6-1-monterrey-sex-and-love-tour |title=6/1 - Monterrey, Mexico - SEX AND LOVE TOUR - Enrique Iglesias - Official Website |publisher=Enrique Iglesias |date= |accessdate=11 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407075013/http://www.enriqueiglesias.com/events/6-1-monterrey-sex-and-love-tour|archivedate=7 April 2014}}</ref>\nEnrique Iglesias has grossed $194 million with Sex and Love Tour.\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = ''Sex and Love''&nbsp;\u2013 {{nobold|US standard version}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Enrique-Iglesias-Sex-And-Love/release/5963118 |title=Sex and Love, Enrique Iglesias: Pop |publisher=discogs.com |date=2014 |accessdate=19 June 2017}}</ref>\n| total_length    = 38:06\n| extra_column    = Producer(s)\n\n| title1 = [[I'm a Freak]]\n| note1 = featuring [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]]\n| writer1 = {{flatlist|\n* [[Enrique Iglesias]]\n* [[Lukasz Gottwald]]\n* [[Cirkut (record producer)|Henry Walter]]\n* [[Rome Ramirez]]\n* [[Pitbull (rapper)|Armando Perez]]\n}}\n| extra1 = {{flatlist|\n* [[Dr. Luke]]\n* [[Cirkut (record producer)|Cirkut]]\n}}\n| length1 = 3:39\n\n| title2 = There Goes My Baby\n| note2 = featuring [[Flo Rida]]\n| writer2 = {{flatlist|\n* Iglesias\n* James\n* [[DJ Frank E|Justin Franks]]\n* [[Carolina Liar|Rickard Goransson]]\n* [[Flo Rida|Tramar Dillard]]\n}}\n| extra2 = {{flatlist|\n* [[DJ Frank E]]\n* [[Carolina Liar|Rickard G\u00f6ransson]]\n}}\n| length2 = 3:18\n\n| title3 = [[Bailando (Enrique Iglesias song)|Bailando]]\n| note3 = featuring [[Descemer Bueno]] and [[Gente de Zona]]\n| writer3 = {{flatlist|\n* Iglesias\n* Bueno\n* [[Gente de Zona|Alexander Delgado]]\n* [[Gente de Zona|Randy Malcom Martinez]]\n}}\n| extra3 = Carlos Paucar\n| length3 = 4:03\n\n| title4 = [[El Perdedor (Enrique Iglesias song)|El Perdedor]]\n| note4 = featuring [[Marco Antonio Sol\u00eds]]\n| writer4 = {{flatlist|\n* Iglesias\n* Bueno\n}}\n| extra4 = Paucar\n| length4 = 3:11\n\n| title5 = [[Loco (Enrique Iglesias song)|Loco]]\n| note5 = featuring [[Romeo Santos]]\n| writer5 = {{flatlist|\n* Iglesias\n* Bueno\n}}\n| extra5 = {{flatlist|\n* Paucar\n* Santos\n}}\n| length5 = 3:33\n\n| title6 = Let Me Be Your Lover\n| note6 = featuring [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]]\n| writer6 = {{flatlist|\n* Iglesias\n* Niles-Dhar\n* James\n* Ramirez\n* Perez\n}}\n| extra6 = The Cataracs\n| length6 = 3:58\n\n| title7 = You and I\n| writer7 = {{flatlist|\n* Iglesias\n* Ramirez\n* James\n* Hollow-Dhar\n}}\n| extra7 = The Cataracs\n| length7 = 3:05\n\n| title8 = [[Heart Attack (Enrique Iglesias song)|Heart Attack]]\n| writer8 = {{flatlist|\n* Iglesias\n* Hollow-Dhar\n* James\n* Ramirez\n}}\n| extra8 = The Cataracs\n|